with answers
============
1. How will you secure a s3 bucket
Ans:- To secure an S3 bucket, I keep it private with public access blocked, control access using bucket policies with ACLs disabled, use access points for fine-grained access, enable encryption at rest and in transit, protect data with versioning and object lock, replicate data for resilience, and enable server access logging for audit and monitoring.
2. Explore bucket versioning use cases and scenarios
Ans:- S3 bucket versioning is used to retain multiple versions of an object, which helps in recovering data from accidental deletions, overwrites, or application errors. When an object is deleted, S3 adds a delete marker instead of permanently removing the object, allowing us to restore previous versions easily.
