Ans:-
12. S3 is a global then why we have buckets region specific
Ans:- S3 is a global service in terms of namespace and API access, but buckets are region-specific because data must physically reside in a region for latency, compliance, cost optimization, and durability across AZs.
13. Multipart upload in S3
Ans:- Multipart upload allows large objects to be uploaded to S3 in multiple parts, improving performance and fault tolerance, and is mandatory for objects larger than 5 GB.
14. Check whether 50tb upload works in multipart upload or not
Ans:- No, S3 multipart upload cannot upload 50 TB as a single object because the maximum S3 object size is 5 TB. Multipart upload only improves upload performance, not the object size limit.
